The course is a training of oral and written expression in scientific French. The training of oral speech involves linguistic and literary topics. The course includes also practical training: the students are required to hand in a certain number of written papers, resumes, reports, essays, articles on their specialty, which are analyzed and commented on by the lecturer, with particular attention on style aspects. 
The first semester will be focused on resumes, reports and summary notes for written expression and on scientific talks in public for oral expression. The second semester will be focused on writing essays on different topics and arguing on the same topics in oral debates.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop the usage of written and oral French and to prepare to academic intervention at conferences.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: 1) can present clear, smoothly-flowing descriptions of complex subjects integrating sub-themes, developing particular points and rounding off with an appropriate conclusion; 2) can present an argument in a style appropriate to the context and with an effective logical structure which helps the recipient to notice and remember significant points; 3) is able to formulate ideas and opinions with precision and relate his contribution skillfully to those of other speakers. 4) can express himself in clear, well-structured text, expressing points of view about complex subjects; 5) can write clear, smoothly-flowing text in an appropriate style, complex reports, articles and papers which present a case with an effective logical structure which helps the recipient to notice and remember significant points.
